      {
        "url": "/case-study/faire",
        "title": "Faire",
        "lastModifiedAt": 1778824527816,
        "htmlId": "articles--faire--4fe71c8efa",
        "sectionRelativeRepoPath": "faire.md",
        "meta": {
          "category": "case study",
          "articleTitle": "Faire secures Macs with CIS benchmarks and Fleet",
          "description": "Faire replaced their previous MDM with Fleet, managing Macs and iPads through GitOps and enforcing CIS benchmarks to improve device security.",
          "publishedOn": "2025-12-11",
          "authorGitHubUsername": "n/a",
          "authorFullName": "Fleetdm",
          "companyLogoFilename": "faire-logo-192x40@2x.png",
          "quoteAuthorImageFilename": "jeremy-baker-120x120@2x.png",
          "quoteAuthorName": "Jeremy Baker",
          "quoteAuthorJobTitle": "Engineering Manager",
          "quoteContent": "“Fleet has opened a lot of opportunities for us. My team is loving managing devices via GitOps, and the built-in support for CIS benchmarks has made it easy to enforce these on our devices.”",
          "companyName": "Faire",
          "companyInfo": "Faire is a global online wholesale marketplace that connects independent retailers with emerging and established brands. Retailers use the platform to discover products and manage inventory, and brands use it to reach a wider audience and streamline wholesale operations.",
          "companyInfoLineTwo": "Faire operates in the US, Canada, and the UK, with about 1,000 employees. Most of their endpoints run macOS, with some Windows laptops, and they also manage 300 iPads used for Zoom Rooms.",
          "summaryChallenge": "Faire’s previous MDM slowed them down. It lacked timely support for new OS controls, its APIs made config-as-code workflows hard to automate, and support responses were too slow to keep up with their needs.",
          "summarySolution": "Fleet replaced their previous MDM for managing Macs and iPads, and supports the GitOps workflows they use to manage their infrastructure.",
          "summaryKeyResults": "Enforced CIS Level 1 benchmarks to keep laptops secure; Migrated 1,000 Macs and iPads to Fleet without disruption; Moved device management workflows into GitOps; Received proactive support from Fleet"
        }
      },
      {
        "url": "/case-study/fastly",
        "title": "Fastly",
        "lastModifiedAt": 1778824527818,
        "htmlId": "articles--fastly--6d4bb88c45",
        "sectionRelativeRepoPath": "fastly.md",
        "meta": {
          "category": "case study",
          "articleTitle": "Fastly gains visibility into all endpoints and critical infrastructure worldwide",
          "description": "Fastly unified visibility across employee devices and global infrastructure with Fleet, migrating 99.9% of Macs in 45 days and consolidating tools.",
          "publishedOn": "2025-01-29",
          "authorGitHubUsername": "n/a",
          "authorFullName": "Fleetdm",
          "companyLogoFilename": "fastly-logo-104x40@2x.png",
          "quoteAuthorImageFilename": "dan-jackson-120x120@2x.png",
          "quoteAuthorName": "Dan Jackson",
          "quoteAuthorJobTitle": "Sr Manager Systems Engineering, Fastly",
          "quoteContent": "“Beyond the technical excellence of the product, the partnership with Fleet has been outstanding. They aren't just a vendor, they are a highly responsive extension of our own team.”",
          "companyName": "Fastly",
          "companyInfo": "Fastly, a cloud computing services provider, operates a global content delivery network and edge cloud platform, serving high-profile media, e-commerce, and technology customers who demand low latency and strong edge control. Their IT team manages a diverse environment of employee devices across Mac, Windows, and Linux, as well as the infrastructure supporting roughly 100+ points of presence worldwide.",
          "summaryChallenge": "Fastly sought to consolidate security vendors across its employee endpoints and CDN infrastructure, and to align its  macOS Management with corporate standards for managing infrastructure as code (IaC). Having control over the endpoint management and monitoring software was also critical.",
          "summarySolution": "Fleet provided Fastly with visibility into all endpoints (employee laptops) and its critical infrastructure (POPs) worldwide. Management with Fleet allowed Fastly to consolidate vendors and to apply an Infrastructure as Code (IaC) approach to managing endpoints. With Fleet’s open-source code base, Fastly is able to continue hosting this critical part of their infrastructure.",
          "summaryKeyResults": "Improved agility when making changes in the endpoint posture with GitOps.; Completed migration in sixty days.; Fleet now enables visibility into both employee endpoints and Fastly’s Points-Of-Presence around the world."
        }
      },
      {
        "url": "/guides/filtering-software-by-vulnerability",
        "title": "Filtering software by vulnerability",
        "lastModifiedAt": 1778824527820,
